# Backend API origin. Required when frontend and API are on different hosts (e.g. dev: frontend 5175, backend 8000).
# Set to backend URL so the session cookie (set by backend) is sent with API requests. Same-origin in production can leave unset.
# Example dev: http://localhost:8000
# Example production: https://your-api.railway.app
# VITE_API_URL=

# Optional: app icon/logo URL. Used for favicon, nav, and QR code. Fallback: /favicon.png (put your logo in frontend/static/favicon.png).
# Use absolute URL (https://...) or path (e.g. /logo.svg). For cross-origin, image must be CORS-enabled.
# VITE_APP_ICON_URL=

# Optional: Admin API key. When set, the admin UI sends it as X-Admin-API-Key for all /api/admin/* requests (e.g. for server-side or script use). Prefer setting in the Agent page instead.
# VITE_ADMIN_API_KEY=
